<font color="#FF0000">SAIGON</font><br>
<tt>Tue Apr 22 23:17:48 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I have not thought of the fall of Saigon in a very long time.  Images and feelings remain in my memory of that event. It was a final chapter of a time, and a beginning of a time, I would sooner forget.  <br><br>
The fall of Saigon? It was a last look at my fragile fleeting pride, sliding, sliding down into a last darkness. Despair, a feeling of lost worth, uselessness, what was it all for? What meaning had that lost year, that flirtation with a grim reaper of souls now transparent against the backdrop of misery laid open like the wound it was meant to be. Images of terror so familiar from another time, innocent faces black with the unspeakable emptiness of abandonment. I feel that abandonment. I feel that terror. I am at one with it this one last time before I, too, escape into a long sleep of my mind. I feel no more.<br><br>
The gray images on the screen fade, and the last of me fades with it. There is no promise of return. I drift, untethered, into the world some call madness, some call escape, some call just plain hell. Saigon, sweet mistress, hope of redemption, the last of me fell with you. We are still bound to one another as one.   <br>

